Shantou Concentrates on Infrastructure Construction
SHANTOU , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- Shantou , a major city in south China 's Guangdong Province , plans to allocate 2.69 billion yuan for the construction of ports , roads , railways and telecommunications facilities .
Shantou Mayor Zhou Rifang said that 1998 efforts of the city will center on completing an international container port , accelerating the second phase port project , and expanding the capacity of both mobile and program-controlled telephones .
Zhou made the remarks during a 1998 work conference on transportation and telecommunications .
According to Zhou , the city is preparing to construct the Shantou-Meishan Expressway , a coastal railway and the Guangzhou-Macao-Hong Kong Railway .
